<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1269</anchor> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-003J</addr><route>erct-003J.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003J.agda" type="external">erct-003J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A \to  C</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1270</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002C" href="erct-002C.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to find a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to the composite <tex>g \circ  f</tex>; we take this to be the composite (<ref addr="erct-002L" href="erct-002L.xml" taxon="Construction"/>) of the underlying <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link> of <tex>f</tex> and <tex>g</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1271</anchor>  <addr>erct-003N</addr><route>erct-003N.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Z.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Z" title="Functions and inverses">Functions and inverses</link> › composition lemmas</title>  <parent>erct-000Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1272</anchor> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002I</addr><route>erct-002I.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002I.agda" type="external">erct-002I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be maps equipped with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> <tex>s_f \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>s_g \colon  C \to  B</tex>. The composite <tex>s_f \circ  s_g \colon  C \to  A</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1273</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>The witness of sectionhood is defined using the witnesses for the two sections.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
