</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>, with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections and retractions</link> given by <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1277</anchor> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002L</addr><route>erct-002L.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002L.agda" type="external">erct-002L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is quasi-invertible, with sectionhood and retractionhood witnesses given by those of the <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1278</anchor> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-003J</addr><route>erct-003J.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003J.agda" type="external">erct-003J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A \to  C</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1279</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002C" href="erct-002C.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to find a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to the composite <tex>g \circ  f</tex>; we take this to be the composite (<ref addr="erct-002L" href="erct-002L.xml" taxon="Construction"/>) of the underlying <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link> of <tex>f</tex> and <tex>g</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1280</anchor> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002L</addr><route>erct-002L.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002L.agda" type="external">erct-002L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is quasi-invertible, with sectionhood and retractionhood witnesses given by those of the <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1281</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002C</addr><route>erct-002C.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link> to coherent <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverses</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002C.agda" type="external">erct-002C.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> have a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> <tex>g \colon  B \to  A</tex> with incoherent counit <tex>\epsilon \colon  f \circ  g \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and unit <tex>\eta \colon  g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex>. We can <em>correct</em> the counit to obtain a coherent <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> to <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1282</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-002C</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The corrected counit <tex>\epsilon '  \colon  g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> is defined like so:</p>
 <tex display="block">    \epsilon ' x : \equiv     \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( f \mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} ^{-1}   \cdot   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta \mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {}   \cdot   \epsilon  x  </tex>

 <p>The coherence <tex>\chi \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon ' \circ  f</tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmas <ref addr="erct-001V" href="erct-001V.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001W" href="erct-001W.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1283</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr><route>erct-000W.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with an inverse as an <em><strong>invertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1284</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000X</addr><route>erct-000X.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Quasi-inverse</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>quasi-inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a function <tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> equipped with homotopies <tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, rendering <tex>g</tex> simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p><p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <tex>\eta</tex> and <tex>\epsilon</tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <em>unit</em> and <em>counit</em> of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>